.TH "snd_ac97_controller_register" 9 "snd_ac97_controller_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ac97_controller_register \- register an ac97 controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ac97_controller *" snd_ac97_controller_register
.BI "(const struct ac97_controller_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned short slots_available "  ","
.BI "void **codecs_pdata "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ops" 12
the ac97 bus operations
.IP "dev" 12
the device providing the ac97 DC function
.IP "slots_available" 12
mask of the ac97 codecs that can be scanned and probed
bit0 => codec 0, bit1 => codec 1 ... bit 3 => codec 3
.IP "codecs_pdata" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Register a digital controller which can control up to 4 ac97 codecs. This is
the controller side of the AC97 AC-link, while the slave side are the codecs.

Returns a valid controller upon success, negative pointer value upon error
